June 10 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Thai telecoms group True Corp <TRUE.BK> is to offer an 18 percent stake to China Mobile, according to a person familiar with the matter. [ID:nL4N0OQ1O8]  * New Zealand's richest man, Graeme Hart, is exploring a sale of SIG Combibloc Group Ltd that could value the world's second largest maker of drink cartons at around $5 billion, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL5N0OQ4CP]  * International Game Technology <IGT.N>, a Las Vegas-based slot machine maker, has hired Morgan Stanley <MS.N> to explore a sale as the gaming industry pursues consolidation to combat slow growth, people familiar with the matter said on Monday.[ID:nL2N0OQ1SV]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]